The changes to `setup.py` does not make sense to me. This would not work for people who just want to work from a copy `beam/sdks/python/`. The location for packaged test data is `tests/data/*', this file not would be included in the tarball. Running the test, after installing the tarball will fail. 

Could you just have a symlink instead of copying files? And until we have a solution could we please revert the change to `setup.py` and include a copy of the file in the `tests/data/` location?

Weird, it looks like the bounded -> unbounded conversion https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/DataflowRunner.java#L338 was not applied. But it was applied when I ran this test locally myself.

OK, I see why it's not working.

I'm setting streaming=true in setup() - after the TestPipeline has already been created. However, creating it also creates the Runner object https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/testing/TestPipeline.java - so by the time I set streaming=true, the DataflowRunner object has already applied the default (non-streaming) transform overrides.
I guess instead we could do something like Flink runner https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/runners/flink/runner/pom.xml#L80
